307697.d: 5.A.6: Use effective intonation patterns, pacing, and delivery when interacting with speakers of the target language in spoken exchanges.

307698.d: 5.A.7: Use communication strategies, such as circumlocution, requesting clarification, asking for repetition, and paraphrasing to maintain spoken exchanges.

307699.d: Skill 5.B: Understand and apply appropriate and varied syntactical expressions in interpersonal speaking.
